  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Qin et al. (2022) present a novel DL-based approach to automate the segmentation of osteons in fossilized bone thin sections, utilizing a DeepLabv3+ based architecture with a ResNet-50 backbone.",
    "The introduction of a dual-resolution strategy enables the model to capture multi-scale features of primary and secondary osteons, improving performance on complex paleontological histological images.",
    "The model demonstrates effective segmentation of secondary osteons, although its performance on primary osteons is hindered by sample size limitations and the inherent distortions in the data.",
    "Despite these challenges, this method represents a significant advancement in the quantitative analysis of fossil histology, reducing the subjectivity and labor typically involved in manual segmentation tasks.",
    "The practical impact of this work lies in its potential to enhance the accuracy and scalability of paleohistological studies, although the model's generalization to other taxa and larger datasets remains a future challenge."
  ],
